Package: kandinsky
Title: Turn any dataset into a Kandinsky painting
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Date: 2017-06-15
Authors@R: person("Giora", "Simchoni", email = "gsimchoni@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package has a single function to turn any numeric vector in the range 0 to 1,
	or a given dataset, into a Kandinsky-like painting, with a few common Kandinsky shapes,
	e.g. rectangles and circles, drawn with wrappers around the \code{grid} package.
URL: http://github.com/gsimchoni/kandinsky, http://giorasimchoni.com
Depends: R (>= 3.3.3)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Imports: grid, purrr, tibble
